args:
The party rescues the dragon named Phantom
and learns he and Felicia are fleeing a being
called Thanatos. The party agrees to help in
this endeavor, but is suddenly attacked by
one of his underlings.
Yes, it's meâ€”and I've brought help!
Those wounds are severe indeed.\nI must treat him at once.
I can't thank you all enough.
They came here to save you.
I see. I'm sorry to have troubled you so.
No sweat, bubâ€”we sent those chumps\npacking like a bunch of luggage!
Ah, I wish it were so...
Uh oh. I know that look.\nSomething's still buggin' ya.
Oh, right, I never introduced myself.\nHow terribly rude of me.
My name is Felicia. Until recently, I had\nbeen trapped in the lair of a terrible fiend.
But Phantom saved me from that life.
It seems this fiend is not eager\nto see you go.
Who cares? We just dropped him\nlike a phat beat!
The foes you defeated were naught more\nthan the underlings of the fiend who kept\nher prisoner.
The one who held me is named Thanatos,\nthough he calls himself the ï¼‚king of death.ï¼‚
He bears the power to take mortal lives.\nHe is massive...and terrifying.
Well, I'm glad you made it out of there\nin one piece.
I am a dancer, you see, and I believe\nThanatos wished to make me hisâ€”\nand his alone.
Yes. In my hometown, it was customary\nfor a citizen to perform a dance to honor\nthe land and secure a bountiful harvest.
Yet because of that, Thanatos set his\ngaze upon her.
So he kidnapped you and made you\ndance for him?
Yes. On the day of the festival, just\nas I was about to begin my dance,\nhe appeared out of nowhere.
Please, you must return me to my village!
You no longer have a place there.
Henceforth, you will exist in this dark\nworld and dance only for me.
Thanatos imprisoned me in his lair,\nand though I tried to escape countless\ntimes, it was impossible.
After my last failed escape attempt,\nI started to think I would never\nbe able to leave that place.
But at that moment, Phantom appeared,\nchallenged Thanatos, and took me away.
And that's when Thanatos sent the\ngoon squad after ya.
You did well to save her, Phantom.
The image of her sorrow caught my eye,\nand I could do naught but help.
Sounds like love at first sight.
Why would you turn the conversation\nto that subject?
Well, if that's NOT the reason,\nI don't understand why you did it.
You've never been one whose sense of\nduty demanded you rush into danger\nand rescue someone. After all, you'reâ€”
Silence, Flamewyrm! Speak no more\non such matters of the past.
I have no specific reason for doing what\nI did beyond base sympathy.
Well then, what are you going to do now?
I will return her to her village.

Simply removing her from danger would
leave the task only half finishedâ€”so I
shall return her to the life she once knew.
After all, it is because of me she is here.
Do not say such things! I cannot possibly\nthank you enough for what you've done.
But Phantom, do you really think it's a\ngood idea for me to return home?
Don't you want to go back?
Thanatos will never stop pursuing me.\nIf I go home, I'll be putting my entire\nvillage in danger.
So while I want to return more\nthan anything, I...
If you want to go home,\nthen that's what we'll do.
If this Thanatos character shows,\nwe'll protect youâ€”and them.
Any chump what calls himself the\nï¼‚king of deathï¼‚ has gotta be more\nbark than bite.
Besides, we cannot simply ignore a fiend\nwho runs about kidnapping innocents.
Even supposing you were able to escape,\nsomeone else would surely become his\nnext victim.
Very heartening, is it not, Felicia?\nThat leaves no reason to hesitate\nin accepting their offer.
Thank you so much, everyone.\nI cannot believe I am asking\nmore of you, but...
Of course. Now then, let's getâ€”
I shall never let you go...
I shall never let you go!\nFelicia, my beloved dancer!
I shall never let you go...\nAnd no one else shall have you!
Where is that stupid voice coming from?!
Focus on the foes before youâ€”they\nserve Thanatos!
He's right... I'm never going to escape!
I said we're going to protect you,\nand that's what we'll do.
Now let's take these guys out!
